      "writtenOn": "2020-06-16T20:35:09Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I like these helpers from a readability stand point, but I think dropping the Make from the function name reads better. I like reserving Make for the meaty factories, etc. and while it does make something, reading a line of MakeFailure() feels weird to me. I like the look of return Failure(...) or return Success(...) better.\n\nThat\u0027s just a small detail, and I like this pattern overall for dealing with the corner case factories that can fail and need to return ownership.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 221,
        "startChar": 22,
        "endLine": 221,
        "endChar": 33
      },
      "revId": "8906903212461ece5fd2f76e8dc8b33f4c851c72",
