        "id": 8341
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-06-16T20:35:09Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This has the same behavior as the old code, but it\u0027s somewhat subtle. Previously, if GrConvexPolyEffect::Make failed, it returned nullptr and that would get returned. \n\nIn the new code, we don\u0027t check the success result and just return fp. Because we pass in nullptr as the input and that\u0027s what the fp is set to on failure, we don\u0027t deviate.\n\nFuture proofing could look like return success ? std::move(fp) : nullptr. WDYT?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 729,
        "startChar": 8,
        "endLine": 731,
        "endChar": 29
      },
      "revId": "8906903212461ece5fd2f76e8dc8b33f4c851c72",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
